<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-17T10:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-17T10:40:00-05:00" n="369" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d369">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1653.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Sullivan</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-17T11:00:00-04:40">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 17, 1914, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Have urged upon Dominican Government all reforms suggested by you and the
                            same are now under consideration. Dominican Government shows timidity of
                            local criticism rather than [?] to grant reforms. I recommend patience
                            and tact for a few weeks when I believe all said reforms will be
                            substantially accorded.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>